# setting up fire base


# 1️⃣ Create Firebase Project
# Go to (link) Firebase Console

# Click "Add project"

# Name your project → click Continue

# Disable Google Analytics (optional) → click Create Project

# 2️⃣ Enable Google Sign-In in Firebase
# In the Firebase Console, go to
# Authentication → Sign-in method

# Click on Google

# Enable it → set a Project support email → click Save

# 3️⃣ Add a Web App to Firebase
# From the Firebase Console project dashboard:

# Click “Add App” → Web

# Give it a name (e.g., mern-auth-client)

# Register the app (no hosting required unless you want Firebase hosting)

